cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DM. 

The paper discusses the trade-off between query complexity and approximation in the context of learning theory and empirical risk minimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The focus on approximation algorithms and PTAS's suggests that it could also belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the mention of "humans providing input" suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
